Follow the below steps to run this example:

Linux
	* First you must be logged in a Linux machine with the root user
	* Second, in the command line go to the 'CreateUserAndChangeFileOwnership' directory and type './gradlew'

Windows
	* This example will do nothing on Windows because, currently, we have some methods that only have effect on Linux
	* Current methods that are ignored in Windows:		 
		- groupadd(..) 
		- useradd(..) 
		- userdel(..)
		- chmod(..)
		- chown(..)
		- ln(..)
		- fixText(..)
	* Current methods that throw exception when run on windows
		- uninstall(..)		
	* For more information, please, see Javadoc of Hook.java